<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-01-26T13:36:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-01-26T13:36:00-05:00" n="1109" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1109">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.6363/207</note>
                        <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Querétaro</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-01-26T12:00:00-06:36">
                                    <hi rend="italic">January 26, 1916, noon</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Department’s January 22. Oil pipe line. General Carranza informed me
                            personally the pipe line in question would not directly or indirectly
                            affect the oil rights of American citizens; that it was intended to be a
                            public carrier to transport oil to the coast for any individual or
                            company that paid for the service.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Silliman</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>